Package: htpdate-perl
Version: 0.9.1
Maintainer: boyska <piuttosto@logorroici.org>
Depends: curl libdatetime-perl libdatetime-format-dateparse-perl libgetopt-long-descriptive-perl libtry-tiny-perl
Files: htpdate /usr/sbin/

Description: HTTP Time Protocol (HTP) synchronizes time with web servers as time source.
 The htpdate utility retrieves the date and time from remote web servers via
 the network. Htpdate works through proxy servers as it behaves similar to a
 browser. Accuracy of htpdate will be usually within 0.5 seconds (better with
 multiple servers). If this accuracy is not good enough for you, try NTP. 
